To the August Ancestral Heavenly Venerable Great Emperor,
Your subject [Name] states: Since the arrival of spring, the rains have been deficient, and I deeply fear the failure of the harvest, which would leave the granaries empty. Though I have gazed toward the celestial realm in prayer, the great rains have yet to fall. Ashamed of my humble and inadequate virtue, my heart grows ever more vigilant.
